FBIS3-475 "drafr045_c_94033" FBIS-AFR-94-045 Document Type:Daily Report 8 Mar 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Full Diplomatic Ties Established With Vatican MB0503174994 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 1600 GMT 5 Mar 94 MB0503174994 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The Vatican and South Africa have established full diplomatic relations. The Vatican said the move would make it easier for Pope John Paul, who often condemned apartheid, to visit the country. The pope is due to make a trip to Africa late this year or early next year.
